  "prompt": "I have forgotten ssc cgl password, what should I do now?",
  "response": "Okay, if you've forgotten your SSC CGL password, here's a step-by-step guide on how to recover it:\n\n**1. Go to the Official SSC Website:**\n\n*   The official website is usually **ssc.nic.in**. Make sure you are on the official website and not a fake one (check the URL carefully).\n\n**2. Find the \"Forgot Password\" Link:**\n\n*   On the login page, there should be a link that says something like \"Forgot Password,\" \"Forgot Password/Registration ID?\", or something similar.  It's typically located below the login form.\n\n**3. Password Recovery Options:**\n\n*   Clicking on the \"Forgot Password\" link will take you to a password reset page.  Here, you'll usually be presented with one or more of these options to verify your identity:\n\n    *   **Email ID:**  You will be asked to enter the email address you used during registration.  A password reset link or OTP (One-Time Password) will be sent to that email address.\n    *   **Mobile Number:**  You will be asked to enter the mobile number you used during registration. An OTP will be sent to your mobile number.\n    *   **Roll Number/Registration Number + Date of Birth:** You might need to enter your SSC Roll Number (from a previous exam, if applicable) *or* your Registration Number (usually provided when you first registered with SSC) and your Date of Birth.  This helps them verify your identity.\n\n**4. Choose Your Preferred Recovery Method and Enter the Required Information:**\n\n*   Select the option that's easiest for you to access (e.g., if you have immediate access to your email, choose that).\n*   Enter the required information (email address, mobile number, Roll Number/Registration Number, Date of Birth) accurately. Double-check that you've entered it correctly.\n\n**5. Follow the Instructions in the Email/SMS:**\n\n*   **If you chose Email:** Check your email inbox (and spam/junk folders) for an email from SSC. The email will contain either:\n    *   **A password reset link:** Click on the link, and it will take you to a page where you can create a new password.\n    *   **An OTP:** You'll need to enter this OTP on the SSC website to proceed with the password reset.\n*   **If you chose Mobile Number:**  You'll receive an SMS with an OTP. Enter the OTP on the SSC website when prompted.\n\n**6. Reset Your Password:**\n\n*   Once you've verified your identity (via the link or OTP), you'll be taken to a page where you can create a new password.\n*   **Important:**\n    *   Choose a strong password that you can remember, but that is difficult for others to guess.  Use a combination of uppercase and lowercase letters, numbers, and symbols.\n    *   Make sure your new password meets the SSC's password requirements (if any, such as minimum length).\n    *   Type the new password twice (in the \"New Password\" and \"Confirm Password\" fields) to ensure you've entered it correctly.\n    *   Save the new password in a safe place.\n\n**7. Log In with Your New Password:**\n\n*   After successfully resetting your password, go back to the SSC login page and use your Registration Number and the new password you just created to log in.\n\n**Important Considerations and Troubleshooting:**\n\n*   **Email/SMS Delays:** Sometimes, there can be a delay in receiving the email or SMS with the reset link or OTP. Wait a few minutes. If you still haven't received it, check your spam/junk folder (for emails) and ensure your mobile network is working correctly (for SMS).  You can also try requesting the OTP again.\n*   **Incorrect Information:** Make sure you are entering the correct email address, mobile number, Roll Number/Registration Number, and Date of Birth that you used during registration.  If you enter incorrect information multiple times, it might lock you out temporarily.\n*   **Website Issues:** Occasionally, the SSC website might have technical issues. If you're encountering problems, try again later.\n*   **Contact SSC Helpdesk:** If you've tried all the above steps and are still unable to reset your password, you will need to contact the SSC Helpdesk.  Look for contact information (phone number, email address) on the official SSC website.  Be prepared to provide them with your Registration Number and other identifying information.  Be polite and explain the situation clearly.\n*   **Document Everything:** Keep a record of the date and time you tried to reset your password, the methods you used, and any error messages you received. This information will be helpful if you need to contact the SSC Helpdesk.\n*   **Security Best Practices:** Be cautious of phishing attempts.  Never share your password with anyone, and only reset your password on the official SSC website.\n\n**In summary:** The password recovery process is usually straightforward. The key is to have access to the email address or mobile number you used during registration. If you're having trouble, don't hesitate to contact the SSC Helpdesk. Good luck!\n",
